ITEM.NAME_EXACT: 5x FFP2 STAR OF DAVIDSON MILITARY GRADE NANO PROTECT
ITEM.DESCRIPTION:
The filtration efficiency is at least 95%. It is a medical device according to Directive 93/42 / EEC and at the same time a personal protective device according to Regulation 2016/425. This respirator with a filter effect of min. 95% preventing the penetration of microorganisms (bacteria, viruses, fungal spores), fine dust and toxic solid or liquid particles from the outside to the inside and thus protects the user's respiratory system. It does not contain an exhalation valve and can therefore be used for normal wear instead of cloth drapes, but with much greater efficiency. Czech production Made of Czech materials 5 layers Long strings Stitched nose clip Packed separately in 5 pieces in a sterile package Non-woven protective coating Dust filter Micro-bacterial filter Nanofiber filter A pleasant material that does not irritate the skin White color Material: cotton + non-woven fabric Nose clamp Comfortable rubber bands behind the ears Protection class: FFP2 Degree of filtration: ≥ 95% Package content: 5 pcs Size: universal Maximum efficiency: 8 hours of full operation Filtration of up to 95% of solid particles of inhaled air Warranty: 2 years INSTRUCTIONS FOR USE: 1) Wash your hands thoroughly before putting on the respirator. 2) Place the respirator close to your nose, hold it with one hand and put the rubber bands behind your ears or over your head with the other. The respirator must fit along the cheeks and under the chin. 3) Replace the respirator with a new one after 8 hours. 4) If you repeatedly put on and take off the respirator, always hold it by the rubber bands and do not touch the respirator itself. 5) Put the used respirator in a plastic bag, which you close and then you can throw it in the basket.
For hygienic reasons, these goods cannot be returned within 14 days.
ITEM.DESCRIPTION_SHORT: The Czech respirator of the FFP2 STAR OF DAVIDSON MILITARY GRADE NANO PROTECT class, which has 5 layers, is designed to protect its user by filtering the inhaled air and to reduce the risk of infection between people.
